  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Africa and LAC Regional (Benin, Guatemala, and El Salvador): Protecting and Promoting Health through Global HIV and Health Law Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve access to high quality HIV-related legal and health care services. 2) To strengthen legal and policy environment for HIV prevention and treatment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Staff in legal service organizations providing free or subsidized legal services to people living with HIV (PLHIV) and key affected populations (KPs) (in Benin); Students and law professors in university legal clinics providing free legal services to PLHIV and KPs (in El Salvador and Guatemala); Staff in the national Office of the Ombudsperson who receive complaints of human rights abuses relating to PLHIV and KPs (in El Salvador and Guatemala); and Prison officers identified as focal points for HIV or health matters (in Guatemala).
Indirect beneficiaries: PLHIV and their family members, KPs and those groups most at risk of HIV infection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed at protecting and promoting health through law.</narrative>
  </description>
